definitions.definition: A girl or young woman , especially a buxom or lively one.
examples: Jane played the role of a wench in an Elizabethan comedy.

subdefinitions.definition: A girl or young woman of a lower class .

definitions.label_groups: archaic , now dialectal or humorous , possibly offensive

definitions.definition: Used as a term of endearment for a female person, especially a wife , daughter , or girlfriend : darling , sweetheart .
A promiscuous woman; a mistress ( “ other woman in an extramarital relationship ” ) .
A black woman (of any age ), especially if in a condition of servitude .

main_definition: ( archaic , now dialectal or humorous , possibly offensive ) A girl or young woman , especially a buxom or lively one.
secondary_definitions: ( archaic or dialectal ) Used as a term of endearment for a female person, especially a wife , daughter , or girlfriend : darling , sweetheart .
( archaic ) A woman servant ; a maidservant .
( archaic ) A promiscuous woman; a mistress ( “ other woman in an extramarital relationship ” ) .
( US , archaic or historical ) A black woman (of any age ), especially if in a condition of servitude .
